new_build_system.doc_string: Creates a new view and populates it with a simple build system boilerplate.

new_plugin.doc_string: Creates a new view and populates it with a simple plugin boilerplate.

new_snippet.doc_string: Creates a new view and populates it with a simple snippet boilerplate.

new_syntax.doc_string: Creates a new view and populates it with a simple syntax boilerplate.

new_file.doc_string: Create a new empty tab in the active window.

args.name: syntax
args.doc_string: The syntax to be set for the newly opened tab. Should be a package relative path like 'Packages/Foo/Bar.sublime-syntax'. Currently, 'scope:' prefixed syntax names won't work.

new_file_at.doc_string: Creates a new empty tab in the active window.

args.name: dirs
args.doc_string: A list of absolute directory paths were the new tab has to be saved. Only the first value is considered.

new_folder.doc_string: Creates a new folder in the given directory.

args.name: dirs
args.doc_string: A list of absolute directory paths. Only the first is considered for creating the new folder.

new_os_tab.doc_string: Creates a new empty window in the os tab.

new_window_for_project.doc_string: Clones the project into a new workspace.

next_bookmark.doc_string: Navigate to the next bookmark in the document.

next_field.doc_string: Navigate to the next field in the snippet.

next_misspelling.doc_string: Navigate to the next misspelling in the document.

next_modification.doc_string: Navigate to the next modification in the document.

next_os_tab.doc_string: Set the focus to the next window in the os tab.

next_result.doc_string: Jump to the next build result.

next_view.doc_string: Sets the focus to the next view by index.

args.name: extend
args.doc_string: Whether to add the next view to the current group's multi selected tabs.

next_view_in_stack.doc_string: Set the focus to the next view in the stack of recent edited view.

noop.doc_string: A non existent command. Use this if you want to unbind any particular key binding & release it to the OS (ST 4117+).
